JOHANNESBURG – Three suspects have been arrested after an armed robbery at Cresta Shopping Centre in Randburg on Tuesday. According to the South African Police Service, a gang of six robbed the Totalsports store. As they tried to leave the mall they were confronted by security personnel and a shootout ensued. One suspect was wounded and another two were apprehended. Police spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo said police were searching for the three men who got away. READ: Motorist killed in crash involving mayoral vehicle Masondo said that no shoppers or shopping centre employees were harmed during the robbery or shootout. A few items were recovered from the arrested suspects. “One firearm was recovered from the suspects and some cellphones that we suspect to be from the robbery were found,” he said. “For now we are still investigating if there were any other items that were stolen during the robbery.” eNCA